data.title: SoCal TACO FEST 2024
data.meta_description: San Diego's 10th Annual Taco Festival at Waterfront Park
data.text:
O.G. Stage

Sir Mix-A-Lot

Sir Mix-a-Lot, is a rapper, songwriter, and record producer. He is best known for his 1992 hit song “Baby Got Back”, which peaked at number one on the Billboard Hot 100.

Treach of by Naughty By Nature

Treach, is a rapper and actor. He is best known as the lead rapper of the hip hop group Naughty by Nature.

Rob Base

Rob Base is best known for the 1988 hit “It Takes Two”, a single that was a Top 40 hit and has been certified platinum by the RIAA.

Young MC

Young MC helped write “Wild Thing” and “Funky Cold Medina” for Tone Loc. Wild Thing would sell nearly 4 million copies and Funky Cold Medina would sell well over 2 million copies.

The Purple Madness (Prince Tribute)

The “Purple Madness” is the ultimate celebration of the most widely beloved entertainer and profoundly influential artist of all-time. Bobby Miller presents an electrifying performance that can be best described as, high energy and a “must see” performance.

FlashPants (80’s Awesomeness)

FlashPants is the #1 MOST BOOKED BAND in California, performing more than 200 shows every year! This HIGH-ENERGY, Vegas-Style 80s Cover Band combines 80s Dance music with audience interaction that will have your people dancing, laughing and making new friends ALL NIGHT LONG! FlashPants is unlike any 80s Cover Band you’ve ever seen!

40oz To Freedom (Sublime Tribute)

40oz to Freedom’ is a professional Sublime tribute band, and winner of the 2010 San Diego Music Award for Best Tribute Artist. 40oz has toured the entire US and Canada for more than 13 years developing one of the largest tribute band followings in the world.

High Tide Society (SD’s #1 Yacht Rock Band)

High Tide Society is a 7 – 11 piece band playing SOFT-ROCK hit songs from the 70’s and 80’s. They cover artists such as Michael McDonald, Steely Dan, Hall & Oates, Ambrosia, Boz Scaggs, Player, Christopher Cross, and many more.

DJ Hurricane Andrew

Hurricane Andrew is Magic 92.5’s Turntablist and Weekend On Air DJ. He mixes all the jams on two turntables from the the 70s, 80s, 90s and early 2000s from 5pm – 6pm with R Dub on the 5 O’Clock Boogie! He has DJed all sorts of events through the years but his heart is still with mixing the Old School Jams for the people!
